{"questionId":"9076700","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The ball is now displaced through a small distance <em>x </em>from the bottom of the bowl and is&nbsp;then released from rest.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4848/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-14_om_06.19.20.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/HP2/ENG/TZ2/01.d\"></p>\n<p>The magnitude of the force on the ball towards the equilibrium position is given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"\\frac{{mgx}}{R}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>where <em>R </em>is the radius of the bowl.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the period of oscillation of the ball is about 6 s.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>ω</em> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{g}{R}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{9.81}}{{8.0}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>9.81</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>8.0</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>= 1.107 s<sup>–1</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em>T</em> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2\\pi }}{\\omega }\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>ω</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2\\pi }}{{1.107}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.107</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =<strong>»</strong> 5.7&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>s<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow use of </em>or <em>g&nbsp;= 9.8 or 10</em></p>\n<p><em>Award </em><strong><em>[0] </em></strong><em>for a substitution into T = 2π</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{I}{g}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mi>I</mi>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076700","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ2.d.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the period of oscillation of the ball is about 6 s.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.1 – Simple harmonic motion","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}